<tr><td>Opinion + size + age + shape + colour + origin + material + purpose + noun</td><td>order of adjectives</td><td>A beautiful small old round blue French wooden desk.</td></tr>
<tr><td>possessive adjective + noun … be + possessive pronoun</td><td>my vs. mine / your vs. yours</td><td>This is my book. This book is mine.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + be + very/quite/rather + gradable adjective</td><td>very good / quite tired</td><td>The film was very good.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + be + absolutely/completely + ungradable adjective</td><td>absolutely wonderful</td><td>The view was absolutely wonderful.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + be + adjective + preposition + noun/verb-ing</td><td>good at / afraid of / interested in</td><td>She is good at maths.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + adverb (mid) + main verb</td><td>adverb before main verb / after be</td><td>I often visit her. She is always late.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + verb + object + adverb (end)</td><td>adverb after verb and object</td><td>She arrived late.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Adverb (sentence) + S + verb</td><td>fortunately / unfortunately / probably</td><td>Unfortunately, I missed the bus.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hedging adverb + S + verb</td><td>presumably / arguably / tentatively</td><td>The results are arguably inconclusive.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Noun + who/which/that + verb (defining)</td><td>defining relative clause</td><td>The woman who lives next door is a doctor.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Noun + , who/which/whose/where/when + verb (non-defining)</td><td>non-defining relative clause</td><td>My mother, who is 65, still works.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Noun + verb-ing (active reduced clause)</td><td>present participle</td><td>The man standing over there is my uncle.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Noun + verb-ed (passive reduced clause)</td><td>past participle</td><td>Cars made in Japan are reliable.</td></tr>
<tr><td>While/When/After/Before + verb-ing/verb-ed, + S + verb</td><td>reduced adverb clause</td><td>While studying, I listen to music.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Never/Rarely/Seldom + aux + S + verb</td><td>never / rarely + inversion</td><td>Never have I seen such beauty.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hardly + had + S + past participle + when + S + past simple</td><td>hardly...when + inversion</td><td>Hardly had I arrived when it rang.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Not only + aux + S + verb + but + S + also + verb</td><td>not only...but also + inversion</td><td>Not only did she pass, but she also got an A.</td></tr>
<tr><td>So + adjective + be + S + that + S + verb</td><td>so...that + inversion</td><td>So beautiful was the sunset that we stopped.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Only then/Only when + aux + S + verb</td><td>only + inversion</td><td>Only then did I understand.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Had + S + past participle, + would have + past participle</td><td>inverted third conditional</td><td>Had I known, I would have helped.</td></tr>
