<tr><td>A/An + singular noun + verb (singular) (generic)</td><td>a/an for generic meaning</td><td>A whale is a mammal.</td></tr>
<tr><td>No article + plural noun + verb (plural) (generic)</td><td>no article for generic meaning</td><td>Whales are intelligent.</td></tr>
<tr><td>The + singular noun + verb (singular) (formal generic)</td><td>the for formal generic</td><td>The whale is endangered.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + be at + home/school/work (no article)</td><td>no article with institutions</td><td>She is at home. He is at work.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + go to + bed/prison/hospital (no article)</td><td>no article with purpose</td><td>He went to bed early.</td></tr>
