<tr><td>S + be/live/fly + above + noun</td><td>above (higher than)</td><td>The plane flew above the clouds.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + be/put + over + noun</td><td>over (covering)</td><td>Put a blanket over the baby.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + verb + beside + noun</td><td>beside (next to)</td><td>She sat beside me.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Besides + noun/verb-ing, + S + verb</td><td>besides (in addition to)</td><td>Besides English, she speaks French.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + verb + like + noun</td><td>like (similar to)</td><td>She sings like an angel.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + work/act + as + noun</td><td>as (in the role of)</td><td>She works as a teacher.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + verb + as + S + verb</td><td>as (in the same way)</td><td>Do as I say.</td></tr>
<tr><td>There is + demand for / need for / reason for + noun</td><td>noun + preposition (for)</td><td>There is a high demand for nurses.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + depend on / lead to / belong to / wait for + noun</td><td>verb + preposition</td><td>Success depends on hard work.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Although/Even though/Though + S + verb, + S + verb</td><td>concession clause</td><td>Although it rained, we went out.</td></tr>
