<tr><td>Therefore/Consequently/As a result + S + verb</td><td>result markers</td><td>It rained heavily. Therefore, the match was cancelled.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Firstly/Secondly/Finally/Next/Then + S + verb</td><td>sequencing markers</td><td>Firstly, we need to plan. Then we can act.</td></tr>
<tr><td>The + noun + of + noun (nominalisation)</td><td>nominalisation</td><td>The implementation of the policy took years.</td></tr>
<tr><td>A, B, and C (same grammatical form)</td><td>parallel structure</td><td>She likes singing, dancing, and painting.</td></tr>
<tr><td>S + verb + adjective + noun (no extra words)</td><td>remove redundant words</td><td>The car was red. (Not: red in colour.)</td></tr>
<tr><td>While + S + verb, + S + verb</td><td>complex contrast</td><td>While evidence supports it, doubts remain.</td></tr>
